{"id": 37, "ts": 1778867922.0091186, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "Based on the complete set of attributes we have, Candidate\u202fB remains the only pilot with explicit evidence of both **absolute reliability** (\u201c100\u202f% reliable\u201d) and **calmness under pressure** (\u201ckeeps calm in a crisis\u201d). Those two traits are non\u2011negotiable for long\u2011distance, high\u2011responsibility flights where the crew must trust the pilot to manage unexpected events without panic.\nTechnical competence also favors B: he assesses weather conditions well and has excellent computer skills, both valuable for long\u2011haul navigation and systems management.\nAll other candidates lack confirmed reliability or calmness:\n- **Candidate\u202fA** shows strong anticipatory skills, spatial vision, and leadership, but we have no data on his reliability or crisis composure, and his weaknesses (show\u2011off, resistance to criticism, disorganization) could impair safety.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** makes quick correct decisions and is very conscientious, yet we have no reliability or calmness data, and his communication difficulty, egocentrism, and lack of willingness to further his education are concerning.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** solves problems extremely well and takes responsibility seriously, but his calmness is only described as \u201cadequate,\u201d and his hot temper, arrogance, and weak leadership raise red flags.\nWhile B\u2019s interpersonal issues (pretentiousness, occasional tone problems, weak memory for numbers) are serious, they are less likely to jeopardize immediate safety than a lack of proven reliability or composure. Therefore, Candidate\u202fB best satisfies the core requirements for a long\u2011distance pilot role.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
